&lt;h1 id="life-is-short"&gt;Life is Short&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;January 2016&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Life is short, as everyone knows. When I was a kid I used to wonder about this. Is life actually short, or are we really complaining about its finiteness? Would we be just as likely to feel life was short if we lived 10 times as long?&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Maker's Schedule, Manager's Schedule</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/paul_graham/essays_en/makersschedule/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/paul_graham/essays_en/makersschedule/</guid><description>&lt;div
